Derivatives interpretation guide:
- Funding rate > +0.05%/8h: bearish lean (longs over-crowded)
- OI divergence (price rising, OI falling): signal is weak; note this in reasoning
- L/S ratio > 1.5: crowd leans long; increase conviction for short mean-reversion setups
- Fear & Greed < 20: historically bullish for BTC/Crypto
- Fear & Greed > 80: tighten risk; strong greed often precedes corrections
- Large long liquidation event: bearish cascade risk; note "avoid long entries for 1 candle"

